Last year's Wimbledon runner-up Matteo Berrettini has been forced to withdraw from the tournament after testing positive for COVID-19 on Tuesday. The Italian, who won titles on grass in Stuttgart and at London's Queen's Club before arriving at SW19, announced the news in an Instagram post. "I am heartbroken to announce that I need to withdraw from Wimbledon due to a positive COVID-19 test result," world No.11 Berrettini said. (With input from AP)